<keyLead id="A41EE7685113B1499FFCFE0F87EFFE29" box="[136,1451,479,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">1. Trees, shrubs, or subshrubs; Ovary inferior .......................................................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F50445D5113B1499FFCFE2C87EFFDCC" blockId="9.[136,1451,479,702]" box="[136,1451,507,529]" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">
<keyLead id="A41EE7685113B1499FFCFE2C87EFFDCC" box="[136,1451,507,529]" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">- Creeping subshrubs, usually forming cushions; Ovary superior........................................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="A41B5CF85113B1499FFCFDC887EFFD59" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">
<paragraph id="1F50445D5113B1499FFCFDC887EFFD97" blockId="9.[136,1451,479,702]" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">
<keyLead id="A41EE7685113B1499FFCFDC887EFFD97" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">
2. Trees or shrubs; Petals 5, glabrous; Stamens 5; Ovary crowned by a conspicuous nectary disc; Fruit dehiscent............................... ............................................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="D8EF3FDE5113B1499A30FDE587EFFD97" box="[1348,1451,565,586]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Escallonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="9" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
