</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F50445D5113B1499FFCFD8287EFFD59" blockId="9.[136,1451,479,702]" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">
<keyLead id="A41EE7685113B1499FFCFD8287EFFD59" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">
- Leafy rosettes to subshrubs up to 
<quantity id="D817E9B85113B1499D6CFD828017FDBA" box="[536,595,594,615]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="105" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
high; Petals 5–7, densely pubescent at the base on the adaxial side; Stamens 5–7; Ovary without an evident nectary disc; Fruit indehiscent .................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="D8EF3FDE5113B1499A28FDBF87EFFD59" box="[1372,1451,623,644]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Valdivia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="9" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2D9B984F5113B1499A28FDBF87EFFD59" box="[1372,1451,623,644]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="105">Valdivia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
